  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency assistance to conflict affected populations in Cameroon: Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of the project is to continue to inform the governmental and humanitarian partners in order to facilitate the implementation of an adequate response to the needs of the populations affected by non-state armed group in the Far North region of Cameroon. The specific objective is to provide, through the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM), reliable and up-to-date information on the number and living conditions of internally displaced persons, returnees and refugees outside the camps, as well as governmental and humanitarian actors to better inform the humanitarian response in the Far North of Cameroon. In order to do so, IOM aims maintain and strengthen its DTM exercise as well as broadening the spectrum of information collected to adapt to changing circumstances and the needs of government and humanitarian partners.</narrative>
  </description>
